\title{Convex Function}
\taxon{definition}
\p{A function #{f : C \to \mathbb{R}} is said to be convex if #{C} is convex, and for any #{x_1, x_2 \in C}, #{\lambda \in [0,1]}, we have
##{f(\lambda x_1 + (1 - \lambda)x_2) \leq \lambda f(x_1) + (1 - \lambda)f(x_2)}
and strictly convex if the inequality is strict.
}
